Summary: Methods for managing buttons, labels, and text input handling in AcceptDialog.

Button: add_button(text: String, right: bool = false, action: String = "")  
Adds a button with specified text, alignment, and action. Right-aligned by default.  

Button: add_cancel_button(name: String)  
Adds a cancel button with the given name.  

Label: get_label() → Label  
Returns the label node associated with the dialog.  

Button: get_ok_button() → Button  
Returns the OK button node.  

void: register_text_enter(line_edit: LineEdit)  
Registers a LineEdit node to handle text input events.  

void: remove_button(button: Button)  
Removes the specified button from the dialog.
