Document: AcceptDialog  
Path: godot/classes/class_acceptdialog.rst  
Summary: Signals emitted by the AcceptDialog class for user interaction events.  

Signal: canceled() — Emitted when the dialog is closed or the button created with add_cancel_button() is pressed.  
Signal: confirmed() — Emitted when the dialog is accepted, i.e. the OK button is pressed.  
Signal: custom_action(action: StringName) — Emitted when a custom button with an action is pressed. See add_button().
