Summary: Class properties and methods for configuring dialog behavior and appearance in Godot's AcceptDialog.

Property: dialog_autowrap (bool) = false
Method: set_autowrap(value: bool)
Method: has_autowrap() → bool
Sets autowrapping for the text in the dialog.

Property: dialog_close_on_escape (bool) = true
Method: set_close_on_escape(value: bool)
Method: get_close_on_escape() → bool
If true, the dialog will be hidden when the ui_close_dialog action is pressed (default: Escape or Cmd + W on macOS).

Property: dialog_hide_on_ok (bool) = true
Method: set_hide_on_ok(value: bool)
Method: get_hide_on_ok() → bool
If true, the dialog is hidden when the OK button is pressed. Note: Some derived nodes like FileDialog override this with their own logic.

Property: dialog_text (String) = ""
Method: set_text(value: String)
Method: get_text() → String
The text displayed by the dialog.

Property: ok_button_text (String) = ""
Method: set_ok_button_text(value: String)
Method: get_ok_button_text() → String
The text displayed by the OK button. If empty, a default text will be used.
